---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	fullWidth={true}
	title="Privacy Policy — phi9.space"
	description="Privacy policy for phi9.space — how we collect, use, and protect your data."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="hero-inner container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated April 4, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="legal-content container">
    <section>
      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect information in several ways depending on how you interact with phi9.space and our
        services. The types of information we may collect include:
      </p>
      <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
      <p>
        When you contact us, create an account, participate in research programs, or use our Lab
        tools, you may provide personal information such as your name, email address, organizational
        affiliation, and any content you submit through our platforms.
      </p>
      <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit phi9.space, our servers may automatically record certain technical information,
        including your IP address, browser type and version, operating system, referring URLs, pages
        visited, timestamps, and general interaction data. This information helps us understand usage
        patterns, maintain security, and improve our services.
      </p>
      <h3>Research and Dataset Interactions</h3>
      <p>
        If you access or contribute to research datasets, motion capture sessions, or other research
        tools provided through our Lab, we may collect metadata related to your usage, including
        session identifiers, input parameters, and output artifacts. We do not collect biometric data
        unless explicitly disclosed and consented to within a specific research context.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Service delivery:</strong> To operate, maintain, and improve phi9.space, the Lab,
          MoCap Rig, and related research tools.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to your inquiries, send service-related notices,
          and provide updates about our research and products when you have opted in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Research and development:</strong> To advance our scientific research, train and
          evaluate models, and develop new features and tools.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Security and integrity:</strong> To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and
          unauthorized access to our systems.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal
          processes.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share information in the following limited
        circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Service providers:</strong> With trusted third-party vendors who assist us in
          operating our infrastructure, analytics, and communication tools, subject to
          confidentiality obligations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Research collaborators:</strong> With academic and institutional research partners,
          only when data has been appropriately anonymized or when you have provided explicit consent.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law, regulation, or legal process, or
          to protect the rights, safety, and property of phi9.space, our users, or the public.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Business transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of
          assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        phi9.space uses minimal cookies and similar tracking technologies. We may use:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Required for basic site functionality, authentication,
          and security. These cannot be disabled.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> Used to understand aggregate usage patterns and improve
          our services. We use privacy-respecting analytics tools and do not engage in cross-site
          tracking or behavioral advertising.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can control cookie behavior through your browser settings. Disabling certain cookies may
        affect site functionality.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described
        in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. When data is
        no longer needed, we delete or anonymize it in accordance with our internal data management
        practices.
      </p>
      <p>
        Research data and dataset contributions may be retained indefinitely in anonymized or
        aggregated form to support ongoing and future scientific work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have certain rights regarding your personal
        information, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The right to access the personal information we hold about you.</li>
        <li>The right to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
        <li>The right to request deletion of your personal information.</li>
        <li>The right to object to or restrict certain types of processing.</li>
        <li>The right to data portability where technically feasible.</li>
        <li>The right to withdraw consent at any time, where processing is based on consent.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below. We
        will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe and in accordance with applicable
        law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, wish to exercise your data rights, or have
        concerns about how your information is handled, please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@phi9.space">hello@phi9.space</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(7rem, 12vw, 10rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .last-updated {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem);
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
